observations.recommendation:
We recommended and Management is agreeable to:
Require the Municipal Accounting Office to enforce the settlements of final and executory disallowances on persons liable who are still active in the service;
Exert extra effort to demand settlement to persons liable who were already retired or separated from the service;
Require the Municipal Accountant to make necessary adjustments on the under-recording of Receivables-Disallowances in the books and to update/correct the subsidiary ledgers of all disallowances with NFDs to reconcile with the GL; and
Strictly require any personnel who intends to resign or retire from the service to settle all accountabilities first before issuing clearances.

We reiterate our prior-year audit recommendations that Management:

11. Direct the Municipal Accountant to submit immediately the lacking disbursement vouchers complete with relevant supporting documents to the Audit Team and henceforth observe the deadline set for the submission of disbursement vouchers and other financial reports as required under COA Circular 2002-003;

12. Direct the Municipal Treasurer to submit all the required reports on time to the Municipal Accountant, and the Municipal Accountant to submit to the Audit Team on the prescribed time for regular validation and verification;

13. Augment the workforce and personnel in the Accounting and Treasury Offices so that required reports are submitted promptly; and

14. Plan ahead the timing of physical count of all properties on date/s nearing yearend to give ample time for the reconciliation of records and avoid delay in the submission of the reports.

